Kyomu-level voice? No—Airi hasn't appeared yet. Just Rei. Alone.

SCENE 2: THE CRACK (1.5 pages)

Evening: Rei walking home. Sunset. Nothing special.

The Moment:

A car swerves. Wrong. The timing is off.

Another car. Same intersection. Should've collided. Didn't.

A pedestrian crosses. Should've been hit. Walks through like nothing.

Rei stops walking. Feels it.

The Paradox Collapse:

Reality glitches for 3 seconds

Colors invert. Sound stops. Gravity flips.

Rei sees:

Himself hit by car (dead)

Himself running (alive)

Himself frozen (terrified)

Himself not there at all

All at once. All in the same space.

When It Ends:

Rei on ground. Not hurt. Not dead.

People walking past. No one stops. No one saw.

But something is different. A weight. A presence.

Airi's First Words:

"That was loud."

Rei looks around. No one.

"Not out there. In here."

He feels it. A voice. Inside.

"You can call me Airi. I'd tell you my real name, but your brain would melt. Not dramatically—just... headache. Nosebleed. Very undignified."

SCENE 3: THE EXPLANATION (1.5 pages)

Rei's Reaction:

Panic. Denial. "I'm hallucinating."

Airi laughs (warm, amused, ancient)

Rei: "Get out of my head!"

Airi: "I'm not in your head. I'm with you. Different organs entirely."

What Happened:

Airi explains the paradox collapse

Reality glitched. He existed in every possibility at once.

When it settled, she came with him.

Not a choice. Not a deal. Just... happened.

Who Airi Is:

Ancient Remnant (doesn't say how ancient)

Has had other hosts (doesn't say who)

Chose none of them. Just existed with them.

Rei: "Why me?"

Airi: "Wrong place, wrong time. Or right place, right time. Depends on perspective."

Rei: "That's not an answer."

Airi: "It's the only one you'll get."

Her Personality:

Carefree, hilarious, Gen Z energy (ironic for ancient)

Rei: "You're... not what I expected."

Airi: "What, you wanted solemn and mysterious? I did that for 400 years. Boring."

SCENE 4: THE NEW NORMAL (0.5 pages)

Next Morning:

Rei wakes up. Checks. Still there. Still her.

Airi: "Morning, sunshine. You snore."

Rei: "I don't snore."

Airi: "You do now. I can hear it from inside. It's terrible."

His Invisibility:

At work, a customer actually sees him for a second.

Rei freezes. Customer looks away. Moves on.

Airi: "That's new. You're becoming visible."

Rei: "What does that mean?"

Airi: "It means people might start noticing you. For better or worse."

SCENE 5: CLOSING - THE WEIGHT (0.5 pages)

Night. Rei on his bed. Staring at ceiling.

Rei: "What am I now?"

Airi: "Same as before. Just... not alone."

Rei: (quiet) "I've been alone my whole life."

Airi: (softer) "I know. I can feel it. Every day of it."

Silence.

Airi: "You want to be seen, Rei?"

Rei: (long pause) "...I don't know anymore."

Airi: "Good answer. Honest."

FINAL LINE (Internal):

"For 1,847 days, I wanted someone to see me. Now someone does. And I don't know if that's a gift or a curse."

